The paper proposes a novel single-shot object detector that aims to balance the foreground-background class imbalance by suppressing easy negatives and increasing positives. This is a common problem in computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces two new modules, Anchor Promotion Module (APM) and Feature Alignment Module (FAM), which are designed to improve the quality and quantity of positive anchors. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the MS COCO dataset, which is a common benchmark for object detection, suggesting that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
